00:45:00.566 --> 00:45:04.764
I also totally can believe that the Fable release was rushed.

00:45:04.764 --> 00:45:17.429
Evidence includes it happening on a Tuesday, Anthropic not realizing people would object to the output downgrading and the general state of the classifiers, and it just happening fast.

00:45:17.429 --> 00:45:21.558
That does not in any way make the export control order okay.

00:45:21.558 --> 00:45:37.664
Yes, This Was A Takedown Order For Fable
Mainstream media has this very strange way of saying that the obviously true thing might actually be true, ya’al, but strictly speaking we can’t prove it and we are a Serious News Organization.

00:45:37.664 --> 00:45:45.855
The Economist: The American government’s primary aim may not have been to control foreign access to frontier AI models.

00:45:45.855 --> 00:45:52.256
Instead, it appears to have used export controls as a convenient way to target Anthropic
Yes.

00:45:52.256 --> 00:46:02.443
This was a way to target Anthropic to get them to take the model down for everyone, and they did not much care about the blast radius of the method.

00:46:02.443 --> 00:46:06.985
They knew full well that this was a de facto full takedown notice.

00:46:06.985 --> 00:46:12.148
That is true even if you are maximally charitable to the government’s case.

00:46:12.148 --> 00:46:22.128
It is in theory possible they were so clueless they did not realize this would be the result, but that’s worse, you know why that’s worse, right?

00:46:22.128 --> 00:46:47.801
